<div id="review_2572163591" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2572163591" />
    <a title="Ray Grasshoff" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3321168-ray-grasshoff"><img alt="Ray Grasshoff" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1551280322p2/3321168.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2572163591?book_show_action=true">Nov 09, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ray Grasshoff" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ray Grasshoff" href="/user/show/3321168-ray-grasshoff">Ray Grasshoff</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780316787031" href="/book/show/693567.The_Nightmare_Years">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2572163591" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13468857760356144209">This book is an eyewitness account, by former American foreign reporter William L. Shirer, of Europe and Germany as Hitler and the Nazis came to power and began World War II. As such, it offers some great insights into how Hitler twisted facts or even made them up for a gullible German public and spineless leaders of England and France during that period. Shirer also offers personality sketches of German and other European officials whom he met and knew over the course of the decade. All in all,</span>
  <span id="freeText13468857760356144209" style="display:none">This book is an eyewitness account, by former American foreign reporter William L. Shirer, of Europe and Germany as Hitler and the Nazis came to power and began World War II. As such, it offers some great insights into how Hitler twisted facts or even made them up for a gullible German public and spineless leaders of England and France during that period. Shirer also offers personality sketches of German and other European officials whom he met and knew over the course of the decade. All in all, it's a great study of this "nightmare" period in world history, and offers great lessons for later times.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13468857760356144209" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


