  <span id="freeText5383551057351360526" style="display:none">I read this book because my father - who is a WII history buff - highly recommended it. Yes, it was informative. Yes, it put into perspective the events leading upto and through Nazi Germany's involvement in the war and how other countries did not listen to people trying to tell them about what was happening in Germany. However, the writing is AWFUL! There are more runon sentences than you can count, comma splices are everywhere, and the author changes thought halfway through a sentence. It made reading this book tedious as I often had to stop and reread a sentence several times to figure out what the devil he was talking about.</span>
