<div id="review_2082304804" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2082304804" />
    <a title="Michael" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1196007-michael"><img alt="Michael" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1212352605p2/1196007.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2082304804?book_show_action=true">Aug 23, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael" href="/user/show/1196007-michael">Michael</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2082304804" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15189988413888286968">In this work, Shirer, most famous as the author of The Rise and Fall of the Third Reich, recounts his time as foreign correspondent in Europe, during the thirties. He and Edward Murrow worked as broadcasters for CBS, giving live coverage of Germany as it took the plunge into World War II, under the Nazis.<br/>As with so much of the history of that time, it serves the dual purpose of observation and cautionary tale. <br/>An insider&apos;s view of how a country, renowned for its culture and science, can disappea</span>
  <span id="freeText15189988413888286968" style="display:none">In this work, Shirer, most famous as the author of The Rise and Fall of the Third Reich, recounts his time as foreign correspondent in Europe, during the thirties. He and Edward Murrow worked as broadcasters for CBS, giving live coverage of Germany as it took the plunge into World War II, under the Nazis.<br />As with so much of the history of that time, it serves the dual purpose of observation and cautionary tale. <br />An insider's view of how a country, renowned for its culture and science, can disappear down an ideological rabbit hole - and drag the rest of the world behind it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15189988413888286968" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
