<div id="review_2715753750" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2715753750" />
    <a title="Alex Anderson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19792055-alex-anderson"><img alt="Alex Anderson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1484964716p2/19792055.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2715753750?book_show_action=true">Feb 13, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alex Anderson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alex Anderson" href="/user/show/19792055-alex-anderson">Alex Anderson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19792055-alex-anderson?shelf=politics">politics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19792055-alex-anderson?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19792055-alex-anderson?shelf=memoirs">memoirs</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19792055-alex-anderson?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2715753750" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4532073424371821845">Shirer is, without doubt, an excellent chronicler of the pre and post-WWII periods, bringing to life with more flair and immediacy this period of time than almost any historian that I can think of.<br/><br/>His incredible gift of being at the right place at the just the right time to act as an eyewitness to history-in-the-making events and interacting with the main protagonists at the time in Europe was phenomenal.<br/><br/>An underrated diarist and writer, well worth reading for anyone interested in early-mid 20th</span>
  <span id="freeText4532073424371821845" style="display:none">Shirer is, without doubt, an excellent chronicler of the pre and post-WWII periods, bringing to life with more flair and immediacy this period of time than almost any historian that I can think of.<br /><br />His incredible gift of being at the right place at the just the right time to act as an eyewitness to history-in-the-making events and interacting with the main protagonists at the time in Europe was phenomenal.<br /><br />An underrated diarist and writer, well worth reading for anyone interested in early-mid 20th C. events, why and how they happened.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4532073424371821845" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
