<span id="freeTextContainer13879439697298904958">Compelling read of disarray in France in the 1930&apos;s, the rise of Nazi Germany, a bit of Great Britain, and Shirer&apos;s life as a foreign correspondent in France, Austria, and Germany. <br/><br/>This is the second volume of Shirer&apos;s three-volume memoir. <br/><br/>Interesting evolution of news reporting from print to broadcast journalism. Wonder how Edward R. Murrow and William L. Schirer would have adapted to blogs, Twitter, and podcasts.<br/><br/>This was an easy, interesting, well written read.</span>
  <span id="freeText13879439697298904958" style="display:none">Compelling read of disarray in France in the 1930's, the rise of Nazi Germany, a bit of Great Britain, and Shirer's life as a foreign correspondent in France, Austria, and Germany. <br /><br />This is the second volume of Shirer's three-volume memoir. <br /><br />Interesting evolution of news reporting from print to broadcast journalism. Wonder how Edward R. Murrow and William L. Schirer would have adapted to blogs, Twitter, and podcasts.<br /><br />This was an easy, interesting, well written read.</span>
